rComments: Terrible prof. No slideshows, long, tedious, readings. Had a discussion period for the lectures, and expected students to regurgitate the content of discussions for midterms. I was in a car accident in the middle of the semester and was unable to attend lectures and discussions for a week or two, and couldn't accommodate me at all. DO NOT TAKE.

This class is a lot of work but very interesting. As long as you do the readings and actively listen during lectures, you'll be fine. He wants you to be critical so don't just regurgitate someone else's thoughts when participating in class
Extremely rude Prof. If you ask a reasonable question, he will look at you as though you are a child. AVOID THIS PROF AT ALL COST.

Grading of analytical questions in exams is harsh (expects only his analysis from lectures to be regurgitated). Overall, he's a cranky, insufferable guy with a big ego who constantly whines about students' "addiction" to technology or about our general ignorance. His hostile, condescending attitude toward students makes for unpleasant lectures.

He has high expectations of the class - which are all fairly reasonable, despite being strict. However, he is extremely rude to students who don't know the answer to a question, a hard marker, and he does not give outlines for assignments. Avoid at all costs

Hard class, harder marker. Read everything, than read more. HOWEVER, kick ass proff and class, he is not interested in you regurgitating the textbook he wants you to have an opinion, think about the material and move beyond silver spoon academia.   Anarchic, left wing, political protester raised in Latin America during IMF restructuring.

Overall a way better class than I expected. The professor really knows his material. If you want to get a good grade, going to class makes it 10x easier. The readings are also really essential and really informative. It is not a difficult class to pass if you attend lectures and listen to what the professor says! The TA was also excellent.

He obviously knows his stuff and the classes were interesting. He expects a lot from you in your exams, and you will use up all the time available and still might not cover everything he/the TA wants you to. I recommend the course because it was really interesting and I learned a lot, but it is definitely not a class you can coast through.

He expected way more detail than was possible to fit into the 5 lines you were allowed to use for answers on midterms.  The expectations for the final paper was not clear enough.  As well he is quite rude, and had a bad attitude if any students got a bad mark.  SERIOUSLY, AVOID THIS GUY LIKE THE PLAGUE.

Florez might be a good prof at the graduate level, but was horrible for a 2nd year class. He doesn't teach, he expects you to have done all the readings for every class and then picks on people to answer. Really tough grader (gave some people 12% on 1st midterm). Asks for the "wider context" but only gives you 5 lines to answer. Avoid if possible.

If you love reading text books take this class! In the discussion groups he called on students to answer and would be very negative if they gave a mediocre answer. Certainly this man knows a lot. But if philosophy isn't your forte then don't bother. One-on-one he is very good, he takes the time to 'splain things. Nice guy, even gave me props once
He is so smart. Really great prof with amazing ideas.

Dr. Florez is the best professor I have ever had! His class was not easy b/c he did not expect his students to memorize information and repeat it back to him - he actually encouraged us to think and be analytical. I am now working as a development professional and I cannot thank him enough for teaching me about the dynamics of culture and power.

Professor Florez is a very interesting man. The class was quite abstract, but once you grasp the concepts it is very interesting. He facilitates some interesting discussions and is always happy to help when you need it! Take his class if you want the opportunity to think about new things!

Professor seems all over the place but if you actually listen and pay attention he has soo much to say and is extremely intelligent. midterms were easy and straight forward if you attended classes. Those who did poorly in his class either didn't pay attention or did not attend class. Final essay was also quite easy.
Any negative comment does more flattery to this guy than he deserves. What a joke. Not a single thing learned, and his hostile attitude didn't help the situation. Stay away.
He is sometimes difficult to understand but the effort is worthwhile because he has a great deal of interesting and important things to say. He taught me a lot about being a good historian.

Extremely helpful professor. If you get lost, see him during his office hours. I started out with a disastrous midterm, talked to him, and he explained his marking scheme. I ended up with an A. I really liked him!
A little unclear, but an excellent professor.
waste of time. hard to understand, all over the place,
the profs lectures did not relate to the textbook at all, and are boring as heck, the good thing is theres no tests, but a lot of writing, if you stick to what he wansts you sure to get a good mark

Wow, worst class of the year. Though he knows what he's talking about, he does not believe in tests, rather weekly assignments and pop quizzes and several essays. He is very harsh with students as aforementioned, and difficult to understand at first. I would never recommend him to anyone.

Steer clear! His lectures usually had little to nothing to do with the corresponding material in the textbook and were almost entirely pointless. He admitted he doesn't usually teach undergrad classes and it shows. He treated students very harshly in class when they didn't do anything wrong. I can safely say I learned almost nothing in this class.
